We understand that face-to-face learning doesn’t suit everyone, so we’ve
developed a range of online learning programs to help health professionals
increase their knowledge and understanding of diabetes. Programs include:
Diabetes Essentials is a comprehensive, self-paced, online learning program
covering all aspects of diabetes from diagnosis to management, including
associated complications. Health professionals who complete this course will
be able to apply their learning to people living with diabetes, or pre-
diabetes, and those who may be at risk. Earn 12 CPD hours.
Nurses play a pivotal role in supporting people living with diabetes. Diabetes
in practice for nurses will provide an increased knowledge and understanding
of diabetes. Nurses who complete this course will be able to have meaningful
conversations with people living with diabetes using health literacy
principles, and have the tools and resources to implement what they learn in
Diabetes in Practice for Pharmacists is a course aimed at improving health
service delivery within all pharmacy practice settings. Diabetes Qualified
collaborated with the Pharmaceutical Society of Australia to develop the
course, it is accredited for 18 Group 2 CPD credits.
To see our complete range of online courses visit diabetesqualified.com.au.
Many of our courses are CPD accredited. If you’re not sure which course will
provide the best outcomes for you, call us on 1300 727 194 and we’ll work with
Beat It is a group exercise and lifestyle program for people living with or at
risk of diabetes and other chronic diseases. It is an evidence-based program
that aims to achieve behavioural change, reduce risk ...
